Persian Gulf Stocks: First Gulf Bank and Saudi Cable Advance

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-11-29T13:37:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/persian-gulf-stocks-first-gulf-bank-and-saudi-cable-advance.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index (DFMGI)  advanced
0.2 percent to 1,370.44, the highest level since Nov. 17. Saudi
Arabia’s  Tadawul All Share Index  declined 0.1 percent at the
3:30 p.m. close in Riyadh.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  First Gulf Bank PJSC (FGB)   rallied the most since Nov.
13, climbing 2.4 percent to 14.75 dirhams. The United Arab
Emirates lender controlled by  Abu Dhabi ’s ruling family raised
the foreign-ownership limit in the bank’s shares to 25 percent.  Saudi Cable Co. (SCACO)   gained the most since April 10,
advancing 5.4 percent to 12.80 riyals. The manufacturer of
cables and reels said it won purchase orders valued at 1.1
billion riyals ($293 million) this month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  